WEBVTT

00:01:15.700 --> 00:01:20.940
=About Love=

00:01:21.000 --> 00:01:23.940
=Episode 3=

00:01:27.290 --> 00:01:28.130
So, how's it going?

00:01:28.380 --> 00:01:30.290
What excuse did you
give your wife this time?

00:01:31.660 --> 00:01:34.020
Hey, sister-in-law's still here.
Can you not talk nonsense?

00:01:34.380 --> 00:01:35.490
Am I talking nonsense?

00:01:36.100 --> 00:01:37.900
Are you denying you're married?

00:01:38.180 --> 00:01:39.130
Are you married?

00:01:41.580 --> 00:01:42.430
Sorry about that.

00:01:42.440 --> 00:01:43.770
I mistook your relationship
with Luanluan.

00:01:43.770 --> 00:01:45.260
How is that a "mistake"?

00:01:45.770 --> 00:01:47.260
Xiu, just tell us.

00:01:47.690 --> 00:01:48.770
Compared to your wife,

00:01:49.820 --> 00:01:51.330
haven't you spent way more time

00:01:51.330 --> 00:01:52.380
with Luanluan?

00:01:52.900 --> 00:01:54.620
Writing songs, gaming,
shopping, eating...

00:01:54.620 --> 00:01:55.770
What haven't you done together?

00:01:55.930 --> 00:01:57.180
Apart from using the restroom together,

00:01:57.380 --> 00:01:58.740
is there anything you can't do together?

00:02:04.190 --> 00:02:05.050
Alright, come on.

00:02:05.050 --> 00:02:05.890
Let's drink.

00:02:05.900 --> 00:02:06.770
Come on.

00:02:06.770 --> 00:02:08.540
That topic shift was way too abrupt.

00:02:08.540 --> 00:02:09.690
If you won't drink, don't instigate.

00:02:10.130 --> 00:02:10.970
What?

00:02:11.100 --> 00:02:13.060
Can't married people
have friends of the opposite sex?

00:02:15.010 --> 00:02:17.450
I feel relaxed and happy with Xiu.

00:02:17.610 --> 00:02:18.690
We really get each other.

00:02:19.380 --> 00:02:20.610
And he's the only friend

00:02:20.610 --> 00:02:22.540
who truly resonates with me
on the same frequency.

00:02:22.780 --> 00:02:23.730
So, what are you two?

00:02:24.450 --> 00:02:25.290
Soulmates?

00:02:33.340 --> 00:02:34.450
Do you still love your wife?

00:02:34.730 --> 00:02:35.690
Of course, he does.

00:02:37.130 --> 00:02:38.610
But maybe over time,

00:02:39.260 --> 00:02:40.100
the passion fades.

00:02:40.940 --> 00:02:42.010
When love gets buried deep down,

00:02:42.170 --> 00:02:43.290
you slowly lose track of it.

00:02:43.570 --> 00:02:44.820
You even know that?

00:02:45.380 --> 00:02:47.130
Truly soulmates indeed.

00:02:48.170 --> 00:02:50.010
I think if you truly love each other,

00:02:50.610 --> 00:02:51.540
you shouldn't need

00:02:51.540 --> 00:02:53.260
to find another "soulmate".

00:02:56.130 --> 00:02:56.970
Sister-in-law,

00:02:57.450 --> 00:02:58.690
you don't know

00:02:58.690 --> 00:02:59.530
what Xiu's wife is like.

00:02:59.820 --> 00:03:00.890
She's a strong career woman.

00:03:01.220 --> 00:03:02.410
She thinks Xiu lacks ambition.

00:03:02.570 --> 00:03:04.220
That's why Xiu's so unhappy.

00:03:04.820 --> 00:03:05.690
And

00:03:05.690 --> 00:03:06.850
his wife really dislikes

00:03:06.980 --> 00:03:08.500
Xiu hanging out with us,

00:03:08.980 --> 00:03:10.100
especially Gong,

00:03:10.340 --> 00:03:11.180
who is unambitious

00:03:11.540 --> 00:03:12.610
and just waits for things to happen.

00:03:13.060 --> 00:03:15.100
But Luanluan's different.

00:03:15.570 --> 00:03:17.570
She plays basketball and games with us,

00:03:17.580 --> 00:03:18.460
and checks out pretty girls.

00:03:18.460 --> 00:03:20.940
With us, Luanluan's genuinely happy.

00:03:21.450 --> 00:03:23.060
In my eyes, it's just

00:03:23.060 --> 00:03:24.340
Xiu and his wife

00:03:24.500 --> 00:03:26.010
met the wrong people.

00:03:27.380 --> 00:03:29.730
Looks like you picked
the wrong time to drink.

00:03:30.410 --> 00:03:31.570
You're insane.

00:03:32.450 --> 00:03:33.980
If you're this unhappy,

00:03:34.130 --> 00:03:35.380
why not just get divorced?

00:03:36.170 --> 00:03:38.010
Come on, that's a bit much.

00:03:39.010 --> 00:03:40.340
Just because it's troublesome!

00:03:41.060 --> 00:03:43.220
Splitting property and all that
is exhausting.

00:03:43.850 --> 00:03:45.570
If divorce procedures

00:03:45.570 --> 00:03:47.010
were as easy as breaking up,

00:03:47.380 --> 00:03:48.410
see if they wouldn't divorce!

00:03:48.730 --> 00:03:49.660
Some people

00:03:50.060 --> 00:03:52.220
think relationships
are like business deals.

00:03:52.500 --> 00:03:53.570
Business.

00:03:54.610 --> 00:03:56.380
Either way, I can't accept that.

00:03:56.940 --> 00:03:58.290
What do you mean by business deals?

00:03:58.290 --> 00:03:59.170
Isn't it true?

00:03:59.890 --> 00:04:01.660
You can't love someone purely

00:04:01.660 --> 00:04:03.540
without any reason at all.

00:04:03.730 --> 00:04:04.610
When you're dating,

00:04:04.780 --> 00:04:06.690
many love themselves more.

00:04:06.980 --> 00:04:09.220
You always judge
how much comfort or satisfaction

00:04:09.220 --> 00:04:11.310
the other person can provide.

00:04:11.410 --> 00:04:13.170
When you accept someone,

00:04:13.570 --> 00:04:15.100
you think it's love.

00:04:15.100 --> 00:04:15.940
But really,

00:04:15.940 --> 00:04:18.220
it's just the result
of weighing all the pros and cons.

00:04:18.460 --> 00:04:20.020
Must you tarnish

00:04:20.020 --> 00:04:21.540
something so beautiful?

00:04:21.850 --> 00:04:23.780
Hey, I never said
your love wasn't beautiful.

00:04:24.580 --> 00:04:26.730
Your love is pure and graceful.

00:04:27.100 --> 00:04:29.930
You love being detached
from mortal trifles, alright?

00:04:30.100 --> 00:04:31.220
Don't drag us into it.

00:04:31.490 --> 00:04:32.340
What about you?

00:04:32.340 --> 00:04:34.170
Have you never loved anyone,
never thought about marriage?

00:04:34.490 --> 00:04:35.370
Actually,

00:04:36.660 --> 00:04:37.540
yes.

00:04:39.170 --> 00:04:40.370
When I was a kid,

00:04:40.810 --> 00:04:42.930
I loved those fairy tales
about princes and princesses.

00:04:43.170 --> 00:04:44.370
And in college?

00:04:44.370 --> 00:04:46.540
I decided Xu Yingying
from the next class

00:04:46.780 --> 00:04:48.610
would be my future wife.

00:04:49.460 --> 00:04:51.370
After work, I dated several times

00:04:51.370 --> 00:04:53.050
for marriage.

00:04:54.170 --> 00:04:56.830
How could I be so shameless back then?

00:04:56.850 --> 00:04:59.020
So purpose-driven?

00:04:59.250 --> 00:05:00.290
Why couldn't I

00:05:00.290 --> 00:05:02.410
just fall in love

00:05:02.410 --> 00:05:04.100
purely and passionately?

00:05:04.610 --> 00:05:06.170
Then, what is "pure love"

00:05:06.170 --> 00:05:07.410
to you?

00:05:07.930 --> 00:05:08.850
For example,

00:05:09.660 --> 00:05:10.610
loving someone

00:05:11.540 --> 00:05:13.930
not because she's pretty or tall,

00:05:14.490 --> 00:05:16.490
but because the sunlight
was perfect that day,

00:05:17.220 --> 00:05:18.980
and she wore a white shirt.

00:05:28.100 --> 00:05:30.460
Are you sure
she only wore a white shirt?

00:05:32.170 --> 00:05:34.170
I'm sure you should
just get out of here!

00:05:36.580 --> 00:05:37.780
Fine, let me put it another way.

00:05:39.140 --> 00:05:40.490
When I met her,

00:05:40.980 --> 00:05:41.930
the sun was gentle,

00:05:42.490 --> 00:05:43.490
and the breeze was soft.

00:05:44.170 --> 00:05:45.780
She smiled faintly at me.

00:05:46.410 --> 00:05:47.850
And she said lightly...

00:05:48.020 --> 00:05:48.860
Wanna hang out?

00:05:50.020 --> 00:05:51.410
I'm about to flip this table!

00:05:51.620 --> 00:05:52.460
Hey, calm down.

00:05:52.470 --> 00:05:53.310
Come on, have a seat.

00:05:53.410 --> 00:05:54.250
Not sitting!

00:05:55.850 --> 00:05:56.780
Then answer me.

00:05:57.140 --> 00:05:57.980
After all this time,

00:05:57.980 --> 00:05:59.460
have you found that "pure love"?

00:06:03.290 --> 00:06:04.130
Yeah, I have.

00:06:05.810 --> 00:06:07.250
Before I met her,

00:06:08.250 --> 00:06:10.490
I truly thought
I'd never be moved again.

00:06:13.020 --> 00:06:13.930
But that time was different.

00:06:22.610 --> 00:06:24.490
I felt like a lovestruck teenager,

00:06:26.050 --> 00:06:28.370
rediscovering everything about romance.

00:06:29.730 --> 00:06:30.850
Totally unprepared,

00:06:31.850 --> 00:06:34.490
I found myself lost
at a foggy crossroads.

00:06:36.660 --> 00:06:37.500
Hello,

00:06:38.410 --> 00:06:39.460
I'm Jiang Yifan.

00:06:42.220 --> 00:06:43.060
Hello,

00:06:43.780 --> 00:06:44.780
I'm Deep in the Alley.

00:06:45.700 --> 00:06:46.540
Hello,

00:06:47.020 --> 00:06:47.930
I'm Yu He.

00:06:48.490 --> 00:06:49.700
Tell me about your boyfriend.

00:06:50.290 --> 00:06:51.580
Though I often

00:06:51.580 --> 00:06:53.170
don't need to cater to preferences.

00:06:53.460 --> 00:06:54.780
But knowing both sides

00:06:55.290 --> 00:06:56.220
is more efficient.

00:06:57.780 --> 00:06:59.780
My boyfriend...

00:07:00.980 --> 00:07:02.410
is a comic artist.

00:07:04.580 --> 00:07:06.540
Why can you accept everyone's love,

00:07:06.540 --> 00:07:07.930
but not mine?

00:07:09.100 --> 00:07:10.900
You ignore me

00:07:11.410 --> 00:07:13.100
and trample my feelings.

00:07:13.730 --> 00:07:16.540
You're stepping on the most genuine,

00:07:16.540 --> 00:07:18.220
the most humble, the most selfless,

00:07:18.220 --> 00:07:19.780
and the most passionate heart
that ever loved you.

00:07:21.370 --> 00:07:23.410
You'll never understand

00:07:23.700 --> 00:07:24.540
what love is.

00:07:25.140 --> 00:07:26.730
(The End. Author: Deep in the Alley)
His pen name is Deep in the Alley.

00:07:27.140 --> 00:07:28.220
Maybe you've heard of him.

00:07:29.170 --> 00:07:30.010
As for me,

00:07:30.460 --> 00:07:32.140
I've prepared
some of his works in advance.

00:07:32.660 --> 00:07:33.700
You can get familiar.

00:07:34.370 --> 00:07:35.810
But don't fall for him, okay?

00:07:36.460 --> 00:07:38.660
I really adore your work.

00:07:39.370 --> 00:07:40.900
Could I meet you in person?

00:07:41.580 --> 00:07:42.610
Please grant me

00:07:42.610 --> 00:07:44.140
this wish of a devoted reader.

00:07:44.980 --> 00:07:46.140
I truly want to know

00:07:46.700 --> 00:07:48.290
what kind of person you are.

00:07:49.140 --> 00:07:49.980
Please, I beg you.

00:07:52.980 --> 00:07:53.820
(Deep in the Alley)
(Alright.)

00:08:14.490 --> 00:08:16.100
You look different from what I imagined.

00:08:16.490 --> 00:08:18.700
You look different
from what I imagined, too.

00:08:19.660 --> 00:08:20.980
How should I address you?

00:08:21.700 --> 00:08:22.900
Just call me by my pen name.

00:08:23.020 --> 00:08:23.930
Deep in the Alley?

00:08:26.930 --> 00:08:27.900
How deep is it, really?

00:08:37.250 --> 00:08:38.420
Alright then, Teacher Alley.

00:08:39.250 --> 00:08:40.250
I'm really curious.

00:08:40.250 --> 00:08:41.610
What kind of stories
have you been through

00:08:41.610 --> 00:08:43.370
to create works like that?

00:08:43.940 --> 00:08:44.890
No stories.

00:08:45.490 --> 00:08:46.940
Just overthinking things.

00:08:47.890 --> 00:08:49.100
Without ever facing real heartbreak,

00:08:49.100 --> 00:08:51.460
how could one paint such tearing pain?

00:08:52.220 --> 00:08:54.340
Your art seems wild and free,

00:08:54.340 --> 00:08:55.890
but if you really look closely,

00:08:55.890 --> 00:08:57.130
it reveals

00:08:57.940 --> 00:08:59.530
how deeply you crave

00:08:59.980 --> 00:09:01.420
simple and pure things,

00:09:02.420 --> 00:09:03.260
like love

00:09:04.370 --> 00:09:05.220
or freedom.

00:09:05.460 --> 00:09:06.300
So,

00:09:06.420 --> 00:09:07.650
if I'm not wrong,

00:09:07.650 --> 00:09:09.060
you must be

00:09:09.530 --> 00:09:10.980
a pessimistic idealist.

00:09:12.300 --> 00:09:13.770
Can you actually feel all that?

00:09:16.940 --> 00:09:17.940
Honestly,

00:09:21.890 --> 00:09:24.100
I genuinely don't get what you mean.

00:09:31.010 --> 00:09:32.300
You've got quite a sense of humor.

00:09:33.580 --> 00:09:35.420
A work reflects
the creator's inner world.

00:09:36.530 --> 00:09:37.650
Your inner world

00:09:37.850 --> 00:09:38.820
is full of romance,

00:09:40.370 --> 00:09:41.210
struggle,

00:09:42.060 --> 00:09:43.610
passion, and conflict.

00:09:44.610 --> 00:09:46.730
You let your characters
speak your emotions

00:09:46.730 --> 00:09:47.850
and debate ideas.

00:09:48.100 --> 00:09:49.100
It's like you're playing chess

00:09:49.100 --> 00:09:50.820
against yourself with no winner

00:09:51.100 --> 00:09:52.730
or a game without victory.

00:09:54.130 --> 00:09:55.100
That's brilliant.

00:09:56.250 --> 00:09:57.420
I don't even know

00:09:57.770 --> 00:09:59.100
why she effortlessly peered into

00:09:59.100 --> 00:10:01.220
the deepest, most hidden part
of my soul.

00:10:05.490 --> 00:10:07.460
The part has never
been discovered before.

00:10:10.130 --> 00:10:11.250
Truly terrifying.

00:10:13.250 --> 00:10:16.010
The heroine is a mercenary gold-digger

00:10:16.010 --> 00:10:18.100
who doesn't understand love!

00:10:20.370 --> 00:10:22.460
The visual reference

00:10:22.460 --> 00:10:24.980
was a cyberpunk-style robot.

00:10:25.300 --> 00:10:28.060
(She fell into twisted values.)
A machine with no human emotions!

00:10:28.060 --> 00:10:29.100
(Everything can be traded.)
Later,

00:10:29.130 --> 00:10:30.530
she fell for another man, right?

00:10:30.530 --> 00:10:31.370
Oh,

00:10:31.380 --> 00:10:33.220
fell in love
without holding anything back.

00:10:33.340 --> 00:10:35.130
Willing to die for him!

00:10:35.890 --> 00:10:37.300
Hey, do you think that makes sense?

00:10:41.250 --> 00:10:42.220
What's your opinion?

00:10:42.530 --> 00:10:44.700
Personally, I disagree.

00:10:45.420 --> 00:10:47.700
Making an emotionless woman the heroine

00:10:47.980 --> 00:10:48.980
(Story Outline 2)
and no dating at all?

00:10:49.460 --> 00:10:51.220
How can female readers relate to that?

00:10:51.650 --> 00:10:53.130
I've told you before

00:10:53.130 --> 00:10:54.890
to draw shoujo manga!

00:10:55.010 --> 00:10:57.490
Make it beautiful! Pure!

00:10:58.180 --> 00:10:59.100
Honey,

00:10:59.100 --> 00:11:00.770
take a break before you keep drawing.

00:11:00.770 --> 00:11:01.610
Have some water.

00:11:02.220 --> 00:11:03.700
Is all this truly worthless?

00:11:04.610 --> 00:11:05.770
How could it be?

00:11:06.100 --> 00:11:07.490
I think it's amazing.

00:11:08.490 --> 00:11:10.030
Why would you think it's worthless?

00:11:10.060 --> 00:11:10.920
Really?

00:11:10.930 --> 00:11:12.300
Look at what you drew.

00:11:12.490 --> 00:11:14.370
The layout, the color choices,

00:11:14.530 --> 00:11:16.250
and your sense of style
are all wonderful.

00:11:16.580 --> 00:11:19.490
See? Especially the heroine's outfits.

00:11:19.980 --> 00:11:21.580
I love every single one.

00:11:21.850 --> 00:11:22.690
I guarantee

00:11:22.890 --> 00:11:24.700
that when this publishes,

00:11:24.820 --> 00:11:26.460
tons of female fans

00:11:26.460 --> 00:11:28.580
will beg for links to buy them.

00:11:28.700 --> 00:11:30.580
Why do you think it's meaningless?

00:11:30.940 --> 00:11:31.780
Look here.

00:11:31.980 --> 00:11:33.530
The hero and heroine's

00:11:33.700 --> 00:11:35.490
height difference

00:11:35.490 --> 00:11:36.940
and your understanding

00:11:37.060 --> 00:11:39.490
of manga aesthetics...

00:11:39.650 --> 00:11:41.420
Did you model the heroine

00:11:41.730 --> 00:11:44.420
after me?

00:11:45.220 --> 00:11:46.340
She's so stylish.

00:11:47.370 --> 00:11:49.220
My boyfriend's so talented.

00:11:49.730 --> 00:11:50.770
Great taste.

00:11:51.180 --> 00:11:52.130
And good looks to match.

00:11:58.250 --> 00:11:59.100
What's wrong?

00:12:01.460 --> 00:12:02.530
Did I say something wrong?

00:12:03.580 --> 00:12:04.530
Are you sure

00:12:06.610 --> 00:12:08.700
this is me? The guy
who sat on the toilet for three hours

00:12:08.700 --> 00:12:10.650
and couldn't squeeze out
even half a line?

00:12:11.370 --> 00:12:13.530
I always thought no one could understand

00:12:13.980 --> 00:12:15.370
my creative struggles.

00:12:18.530 --> 00:12:20.730
Did sitting for three hours
not give you hemorrhoids?

00:12:23.490 --> 00:12:24.330
Honestly,

00:12:24.340 --> 00:12:25.890
I've reread every work of yours

00:12:26.180 --> 00:12:27.250
many times.

00:12:27.890 --> 00:12:29.530
Countless rereads.

00:12:30.250 --> 00:12:31.980
Each time brings new meaning,

00:12:32.180 --> 00:12:33.180
richer with depth.

00:12:35.180 --> 00:12:36.020
So,

00:12:36.580 --> 00:12:38.460
meeting you today

00:12:40.220 --> 00:12:41.300
makes me incredibly happy.

00:12:43.490 --> 00:12:44.980
Which work is your favorite?

00:12:45.300 --> 00:12:46.140
The Selling Madame.

00:12:49.890 --> 00:12:50.770
That one, huh?

00:12:54.980 --> 00:12:55.820
Are you sure about that?

00:12:56.220 --> 00:12:57.980
I actually reread it before coming.

00:12:58.100 --> 00:12:58.940
Oh?

00:12:59.300 --> 00:13:00.200
The breathtaking heroine

00:13:00.210 --> 00:13:01.820
you created

00:13:02.730 --> 00:13:04.100
is incredibly complex.

00:13:06.530 --> 00:13:08.130
All those men drawn

00:13:08.460 --> 00:13:09.940
to her smile,

00:13:10.130 --> 00:13:11.060
her words,

00:13:11.770 --> 00:13:14.220
even silently being near her,

00:13:14.580 --> 00:13:15.820
filled them

00:13:15.830 --> 00:13:18.490
with immense satisfaction and vanity.

00:13:19.420 --> 00:13:20.260
Gradually,

00:13:20.490 --> 00:13:22.530
she began selling her listening

00:13:22.850 --> 00:13:23.690
and companionship.

00:13:25.180 --> 00:13:27.460
From this trade, she gained money

00:13:28.100 --> 00:13:30.700
and a triumphant thrill.

00:13:31.650 --> 00:13:33.460
She fell into twisted values.

00:13:34.180 --> 00:13:37.100
And she believes everything
in the world can be traded.

00:13:39.100 --> 00:13:42.890
She saw herself
as an inexhaustible currency.

00:13:43.850 --> 00:13:44.940
I love you.

00:13:47.530 --> 00:13:48.650
Until one day,

00:13:48.980 --> 00:13:50.460
she tried selling love.

00:13:51.100 --> 00:13:52.060
That's when she realized

00:13:52.250 --> 00:13:54.060
that love can't be traded.

00:13:54.890 --> 00:13:56.820
She couldn't fake loving someone.

00:13:57.340 --> 00:13:59.530
So, she received
rejection and bad reviews

00:13:59.770 --> 00:14:01.940
from those she didn't love.

00:14:03.220 --> 00:14:05.370
She started doubting herself.

00:14:06.730 --> 00:14:08.010
The cruelest part?

00:14:08.420 --> 00:14:10.610
She met the man
who made her forget her worth,

00:14:10.770 --> 00:14:12.890
the one she'd give herself to

00:14:13.100 --> 00:14:14.300
unconditionally.

00:14:15.180 --> 00:14:18.180
But that man felt nothing for her.

00:14:21.300 --> 00:14:22.220
I love you.

00:14:24.060 --> 00:14:25.490
He was even deeply repulsed.

00:14:33.700 --> 00:14:35.100
Her world was shattered.

00:14:40.940 --> 00:14:42.460
She had always been proud.

00:14:43.060 --> 00:14:44.300
But in the face of love,

00:14:44.490 --> 00:14:45.730
she felt utterly worthless.

00:14:47.370 --> 00:14:49.730
In the end, her life and her values

00:14:50.220 --> 00:14:51.340
perished

00:14:51.700 --> 00:14:52.610
together.

00:14:59.700 --> 00:15:01.580
The heroine seems frivolous,

00:15:01.580 --> 00:15:03.530
but her heart is flawless,

00:15:03.820 --> 00:15:06.580
single-mindedly pursuing
her vision of happiness.

00:15:08.180 --> 00:15:09.220
Happiness is like

00:15:09.220 --> 00:15:10.980
the anglerfish's lure-light,

00:15:11.420 --> 00:15:13.250
giving hope yet breeding despair.

00:15:15.980 --> 00:15:17.650
But why does

00:15:19.220 --> 00:15:20.130
this inexplicable feeling

00:15:22.300 --> 00:15:23.370
sprout now?

00:15:24.730 --> 00:15:25.700
At this inappropriate moment?

00:15:29.180 --> 00:15:30.130
I like...

00:15:34.980 --> 00:15:36.770
your incisive analysis.

00:15:44.420 --> 00:15:46.100
Can I ask you something personal?

00:15:47.530 --> 00:15:48.370
Go ahead.

00:15:49.300 --> 00:15:50.370
Do you have a girlfriend?

00:15:51.370 --> 00:15:52.420
Do you have a boyfriend?

00:15:52.420 --> 00:15:53.280
No.

00:15:53.290 --> 00:15:54.230
Now you do.

00:16:01.300 --> 00:16:02.370
Just kidding.

00:16:04.130 --> 00:16:05.180
Actually, I do have a girlfriend.

00:16:17.730 --> 00:16:18.650
I figured.

00:16:20.130 --> 00:16:21.580
But for me,

00:16:23.060 --> 00:16:24.220
that's kind of bad news.

00:16:26.730 --> 00:16:27.570
Oh?

00:16:28.940 --> 00:16:30.490
Since first seeing your work,

00:16:30.490 --> 00:16:31.370
I just knew

00:16:34.060 --> 00:16:34.900
that I liked you.

00:16:36.580 --> 00:16:38.060
I spent a whole day,

00:16:38.460 --> 00:16:39.650
a full 24 hours,

00:16:39.650 --> 00:16:41.010
finishing reading all your works.

00:16:41.010 --> 00:16:42.420
I remember it was...

00:16:42.890 --> 00:16:44.180
around 4 AM.

00:16:44.610 --> 00:16:45.730
Excitedly, I called my best friend.

00:16:45.730 --> 00:16:47.420
And I told her on the phone,

00:16:47.980 --> 00:16:49.180
"I've fallen for a comic artist."

00:16:52.460 --> 00:16:53.300
"I'm in love."

00:16:58.850 --> 00:16:59.940
Jiang Yifan, right?

00:17:01.370 --> 00:17:02.300
I think

00:17:02.770 --> 00:17:04.860
you only like my work.
That doesn't mean...

00:17:04.860 --> 00:17:06.490
Isn't your work your inner voice?

00:17:06.940 --> 00:17:07.780
Don't deny it.

00:17:09.180 --> 00:17:10.020
I get it.

00:17:12.860 --> 00:17:14.940
I'm sure you're the one who moves me.

00:17:17.140 --> 00:17:18.290
You might

00:17:18.980 --> 00:17:20.050
think me rash,

00:17:20.050 --> 00:17:21.140
even crazy.

00:17:21.420 --> 00:17:22.660
But...

00:17:22.660 --> 00:17:23.660
But this feeling is real.

00:17:29.010 --> 00:17:29.850
I'm sure...

00:17:33.980 --> 00:17:34.860
I've fallen for you.

00:17:43.660 --> 00:17:45.460
I appreciate your affection, truly.

00:17:46.660 --> 00:17:47.500
Thank you.

00:17:48.330 --> 00:17:50.290
But... what do you want me to do?

00:17:50.860 --> 00:17:51.980
Break up with my girlfriend?

00:17:52.180 --> 00:17:53.020
Be with you?

00:17:54.010 --> 00:17:55.050
I don't know.

00:17:56.730 --> 00:17:58.250
I'm not unreasonable.

00:17:58.490 --> 00:18:00.220
I came just

00:18:00.900 --> 00:18:02.420
to be honest about my feelings.

00:18:03.530 --> 00:18:04.940
Can I ask you one more thing?

00:18:06.140 --> 00:18:06.980
Just one last question.

00:18:16.090 --> 00:18:17.460
Have you ever,

00:18:19.490 --> 00:18:20.940
even slightly,

00:18:21.570 --> 00:18:22.620
a tiny bit,

00:18:23.860 --> 00:18:25.180
felt anything for me?

00:18:30.140 --> 00:18:31.730
If I turned and left now,

00:18:34.010 --> 00:18:34.940
would you stop me?

00:18:55.660 --> 00:18:56.500
Ah?

00:18:57.620 --> 00:18:59.050
I think you're being too impulsive.

00:18:59.290 --> 00:19:00.810
This is only our first meeting.

00:19:00.880 --> 00:19:01.720
- Regarding feelings...
- Teacher Alley,

00:19:01.730 --> 00:19:03.490
thank you for taking the time to see me.

00:19:03.770 --> 00:19:04.660
It's a great honor.

00:19:05.290 --> 00:19:06.130
I won't disturb you anymore.

00:19:15.700 --> 00:19:16.540
Wait a moment!

00:19:18.810 --> 00:19:19.650
This move...

00:19:21.330 --> 00:19:22.180
She's really tough.

00:19:25.570 --> 00:19:27.570
Has anyone ever said you're arrogant?

00:19:28.250 --> 00:19:29.700
Those who pursued me

00:19:29.860 --> 00:19:31.140
thought I was aloof.

00:19:31.290 --> 00:19:33.090
Friends who love me think I'm cute.

00:19:33.420 --> 00:19:35.860
Those who envy me complain
that I'm too pretty.

00:19:36.010 --> 00:19:38.490
You're the first one
to call me arrogant.

00:19:38.730 --> 00:19:39.900
I'm not complimenting you.

00:19:40.490 --> 00:19:42.660
And I think you're quite annoying.

00:19:45.180 --> 00:19:46.050
Teacher Alley,

00:19:46.050 --> 00:19:46.900
oh no,

00:19:46.900 --> 00:19:48.250
I should call you my dear,

00:19:48.770 --> 00:19:50.140
or maybe, honey.

00:19:50.530 --> 00:19:51.490
Do you think

00:19:51.490 --> 00:19:52.980
being easily won over

00:19:52.980 --> 00:19:54.490
by a little minx like me

00:19:55.010 --> 00:19:56.050
is very unsatisfying?

00:19:57.010 --> 00:19:57.900
Childish.

00:19:57.900 --> 00:19:59.490
I haven't agreed to anything.

00:20:01.810 --> 00:20:04.250
Are all you men so good at pretending?

00:20:04.490 --> 00:20:06.010
If you like someone, just say it.

00:20:06.140 --> 00:20:07.380
Is it embarrassing?

00:20:07.940 --> 00:20:08.940
Jiang Yifan,

00:20:09.250 --> 00:20:11.660
you seem to have forgotten
I have a girlfriend.

00:20:12.050 --> 00:20:13.620
Oh, I really did forget
if you hadn't said so.

00:20:14.050 --> 00:20:15.620
Teacher Alley has a girlfriend.

00:20:15.620 --> 00:20:17.180
Why aren't you obediently
spending time with her?

00:20:17.330 --> 00:20:19.570
Instead, you're out
on a date with another girl.

00:20:19.810 --> 00:20:20.900
That's outrageous.

00:20:21.810 --> 00:20:24.730
It's just normal interaction
with a friend of the opposite sex.

00:20:25.050 --> 00:20:27.220
She has that much trust in me.

00:20:27.940 --> 00:20:29.420
When we're together,

00:20:29.420 --> 00:20:31.180
let's not mention your girlfriend, okay?

00:20:31.940 --> 00:20:33.010
Even I

00:20:33.420 --> 00:20:34.730
might get jealous.

00:20:41.700 --> 00:20:43.620
If you had met me before her,

00:20:45.490 --> 00:20:46.700
would you have fallen in love with me?

00:20:47.940 --> 00:20:49.460
If you were my girlfriend,

00:20:50.380 --> 00:20:51.620
you definitely wouldn't
want me to answer

00:20:51.620 --> 00:20:53.140
that kind of question from another girl.

00:20:53.900 --> 00:20:54.740
So,

00:20:56.250 --> 00:20:57.250
there are no ifs.

00:20:58.180 --> 00:21:00.570
My boyfriend is

00:21:01.940 --> 00:21:03.460
a very cunning old fox.

00:21:03.940 --> 00:21:07.180
He seems unusually wary

00:21:07.180 --> 00:21:08.250
of overly proactive girls.

00:21:08.460 --> 00:21:09.980
But I know it very well.

00:21:10.420 --> 00:21:11.570
He has never stopped

00:21:11.570 --> 00:21:13.050
interacting with other girls.

00:21:13.420 --> 00:21:14.810
I just can't catch him red-handed.

00:21:21.770 --> 00:21:23.730
Did you drink too much to even draw now?

00:21:24.770 --> 00:21:26.900
Ah, I'd really love to see you draw.

00:21:27.140 --> 00:21:30.140
They say drinking
can inspire creativity.

00:21:31.220 --> 00:21:32.420
But my creative process

00:21:32.420 --> 00:21:33.700
is too dull and boring.

00:21:33.980 --> 00:21:35.010
Are you sure you want to watch?

00:21:35.860 --> 00:21:37.980
But a man is the most charming

00:21:38.090 --> 00:21:39.940
when he's focused on something.

00:21:42.380 --> 00:21:44.010
What I'm curious about is,

00:21:45.250 --> 00:21:46.940
what do you want to see me focus on?

00:21:48.490 --> 00:21:49.810
Facing your temptation,

00:21:49.980 --> 00:21:51.490
he might pretend to be profound,

00:21:51.490 --> 00:21:52.900
acting very calm.

00:21:53.460 --> 00:21:55.250
But if you are too proactive,

00:21:55.250 --> 00:21:56.620
he can easily detect it.

00:21:56.980 --> 00:21:57.820
So,

00:21:57.940 --> 00:21:59.900
your persistent attitude
and proactive limits

00:21:59.900 --> 00:22:01.050
must be perfectly measured.

00:22:01.220 --> 00:22:02.090
Otherwise,

00:22:02.460 --> 00:22:05.050
you won't catch a shred of evidence.

00:22:05.570 --> 00:22:06.860
You just need to tell me

00:22:07.770 --> 00:22:08.900
how you want me to do it.

00:22:09.660 --> 00:22:11.090
No matter what it takes,

00:22:11.810 --> 00:22:12.770
this time,

00:22:14.860 --> 00:22:16.380
I want to catch him in the act.

00:22:17.050 --> 00:22:18.570
Sorry, I can't agree to that.

00:22:19.490 --> 00:22:21.290
No, I didn't mean it that way.

00:22:21.290 --> 00:22:22.220
If it were really like that,

00:22:22.220 --> 00:22:23.530
I couldn't accept it more than you.

00:22:28.090 --> 00:22:29.460
I just want

00:22:30.980 --> 00:22:32.140
to create a situation

00:22:32.460 --> 00:22:34.250
where he can't argue his way out.

00:22:35.660 --> 00:22:37.220
I want him to be so ashamed

00:22:38.290 --> 00:22:39.620
and defeated that
he'll never dare hurt me.

00:23:05.730 --> 00:23:07.570
I didn't expect
your home to be so clean.

00:23:11.660 --> 00:23:14.730
Wow, you've got
so many plush toys. How cute.

00:23:27.940 --> 00:23:28.940
What would you like to drink?

00:23:31.010 --> 00:23:32.810
Ah, anything's fine.

00:23:34.940 --> 00:23:36.900
Is this where you usually create?

00:23:37.140 --> 00:23:37.980
Yeah.

00:23:52.010 --> 00:23:54.220
To be a radiant and flamboyant man.

00:23:54.380 --> 00:23:55.810
Not toppling kingdoms,
not captivating cities.

00:23:55.810 --> 00:23:56.660
Devoting everything

00:23:56.660 --> 00:23:58.770
to having a good time
with the beloved girl.

00:23:59.980 --> 00:24:01.730
This wouldn't be your motto, would it?

00:24:01.730 --> 00:24:02.900
Just a line from the script.

00:24:03.330 --> 00:24:04.380
It's for the plot.

00:24:24.140 --> 00:24:25.940
Do you need that now?

00:26:03.140 --> 00:26:03.980
Open the door.

00:26:05.330 --> 00:26:06.170
Open up!

00:26:06.900 --> 00:26:08.090
Is someone knocking?

00:26:08.620 --> 00:26:09.620
I know you're inside.

00:26:09.620 --> 00:26:11.330
Why did you lock it?

00:26:13.220 --> 00:26:14.220
Open the door!

00:26:14.530 --> 00:26:15.370
It's okay.

00:26:15.530 --> 00:26:16.420
Let me in.

00:26:16.530 --> 00:26:17.530
Ignore her.

00:26:18.810 --> 00:26:19.860
Is there a woman inside?

00:26:19.860 --> 00:26:21.460
Could it be your girlfriend?

00:26:21.460 --> 00:26:23.290
Why... would she come now?

00:26:23.340 --> 00:26:24.220
Open the door!

00:26:24.220 --> 00:26:25.060
What's wrong?

00:26:26.570 --> 00:26:27.530
Didn't you say that

00:26:27.770 --> 00:26:29.620
- you would do something romantic with me?
- Open the door!

00:26:30.500 --> 00:26:31.380
Open it!

00:26:31.380 --> 00:26:32.420
Wait, are you crazy?

00:26:33.570 --> 00:26:35.220
- Open the door!
- Your girlfriend is at the door.

00:26:36.220 --> 00:26:37.060
Open the door!

00:26:37.290 --> 00:26:38.250
- I know there's a woman inside.
- So what?

00:26:38.250 --> 00:26:39.090
Open the door!

00:26:39.090 --> 00:26:41.050
I should get dressed
and open it for her.

00:26:41.050 --> 00:26:41.890
Open it!

00:26:42.250 --> 00:26:43.570
Then I'll explain to her

00:26:43.570 --> 00:26:45.220
- that you and I did nothing.
- Open the door!

00:26:45.770 --> 00:26:46.770
Do you think she'll believe it?

00:26:49.490 --> 00:26:52.220
- If it's bound to be a hopeless verdict,
- Open the door!

00:26:53.290 --> 00:26:54.770
we shouldn't let it
turn into a misunderstanding.

00:26:54.770 --> 00:26:56.140
What are you doing inside?

00:26:56.250 --> 00:26:57.700
- Don't you agree?
- Open the door!

00:26:59.700 --> 00:27:00.770
No, Teacher Alley.

00:27:02.900 --> 00:27:04.010
I admit I love you deeply.

00:27:05.010 --> 00:27:06.490
But in this current situation,

00:27:06.810 --> 00:27:07.860
I'm really not interested.

00:27:07.980 --> 00:27:08.820
Open the door!

00:27:11.490 --> 00:27:12.330
Open the door.

00:27:13.980 --> 00:27:14.940
Open the door!

00:27:19.290 --> 00:27:20.130
It's fine.

00:27:21.770 --> 00:27:23.490
Then let's go with your original plan.

00:27:24.860 --> 00:27:25.700
Open the door.

00:27:29.660 --> 00:27:30.570
Open the door!

00:27:30.570 --> 00:27:31.530
What are you saying?

00:27:32.090 --> 00:27:33.010
- Nothing.
- Open the door!

00:27:33.330 --> 00:27:34.900
I'll open the door,
and she's here to catch us.

00:27:34.900 --> 00:27:35.750
Open the door!

00:27:35.750 --> 00:27:37.570
You walk away unscathed,
and I bear all the blame.

00:27:38.250 --> 00:27:39.290
Is this what you wanted,

00:27:41.090 --> 00:27:42.770
what both of you wanted as the climax?

00:27:48.380 --> 00:27:49.860
I don't understand what you're saying.

00:27:53.010 --> 00:27:54.140
I really wish

00:27:54.860 --> 00:27:55.730
I didn't know either.

00:27:56.530 --> 00:27:58.250
But I can't pretend to be ignorant.

00:27:59.530 --> 00:28:00.420
I actually admire you.

00:28:00.980 --> 00:28:03.220
You played

00:28:03.220 --> 00:28:04.570
a crazy yet rational pursuer.

00:28:05.290 --> 00:28:06.130
But...

00:28:07.250 --> 00:28:09.180
the lines analyzing my work

00:28:09.180 --> 00:28:10.980
seem a bit rehearsed and slightly stiff.

00:28:12.250 --> 00:28:13.180
For the rest of the pacing,

00:28:13.180 --> 00:28:14.860
you handled it with perfect tension

00:28:15.290 --> 00:28:16.250
and timing.

00:28:16.940 --> 00:28:19.260
You portrayed
the character, Jiang Yifan,

00:28:20.250 --> 00:28:21.090
successfully.

00:28:23.290 --> 00:28:24.860
What are you doing inside?

00:28:25.530 --> 00:28:26.370
Open the door!

00:28:32.290 --> 00:28:34.490
I know comic artists are imaginative.

00:28:35.460 --> 00:28:36.300
But

00:28:37.220 --> 00:28:38.490
you're overly sensitive.

00:28:38.490 --> 00:28:39.770
Open the door and let me in.

00:28:42.980 --> 00:28:43.940
Open the door!

00:28:44.940 --> 00:28:46.140
Your setting

00:28:46.860 --> 00:28:48.140
has a fatal flaw.

00:28:49.050 --> 00:28:50.180
Open the door!

00:28:52.810 --> 00:28:54.050
The Selling Madame.

00:28:54.050 --> 00:28:54.890
Open the door!

00:28:56.090 --> 00:28:58.090
I've never published this work.

00:28:59.810 --> 00:29:01.140
Where did you see it?

00:29:07.530 --> 00:29:08.420
As for me,

00:29:08.660 --> 00:29:11.140
I've prepared
some of his works in advance.

00:29:11.490 --> 00:29:12.530
You can get familiar.

00:29:12.700 --> 00:29:14.010
Which work is your favorite?

00:29:14.250 --> 00:29:15.140
The Selling Madame.

00:29:17.180 --> 00:29:18.490
Have you ever,

00:29:19.730 --> 00:29:21.220
even slightly,

00:29:21.860 --> 00:29:22.810
a tiny bit,

00:29:24.090 --> 00:29:25.290
felt anything for me?

00:29:26.290 --> 00:29:28.180
You looked completely invested
when you lied.

00:29:30.140 --> 00:29:31.700
How could I bear to let you lose?

00:29:37.660 --> 00:29:39.980
(Yu He)

00:29:46.140 --> 00:29:47.860
You're not answering my calls, are you?

00:29:49.330 --> 00:29:51.180
You're ignoring my calls, right?

00:29:53.090 --> 00:29:54.530
Aren't you going to explain yourself?

00:30:04.570 --> 00:30:06.490
Jiang Yifan, you're an emotional fraud!

00:30:07.460 --> 00:30:08.660
What are you doing here?

00:30:09.530 --> 00:30:10.940
What are you doing?

00:30:13.250 --> 00:30:14.180
But I don't blame you.

00:30:17.660 --> 00:30:19.010
I'm just a bit sad.

00:30:21.940 --> 00:30:23.330
Turns out you never loved me at all.

00:30:25.080 --> 00:30:25.940
Open the door!

00:30:25.940 --> 00:30:28.050
Not even a little fondness
for me, is there?

00:30:31.010 --> 00:30:31.860
But why?

00:30:33.220 --> 00:30:34.420
Why did you say you loved me?

00:30:35.530 --> 00:30:36.460
I took it seriously.

00:30:47.900 --> 00:30:49.380
Do you know what you're saying?

00:30:50.810 --> 00:30:52.940
Saying that, aren't you afraid
of hurting your girlfriend?

00:30:53.090 --> 00:30:54.180
When you said you loved me,

00:30:54.180 --> 00:30:55.530
weren't you afraid of hurting me?

00:30:55.530 --> 00:30:57.140
You have a girlfriend.

00:30:57.710 --> 00:30:59.280
You could have just rejected me.

00:31:00.940 --> 00:31:01.900
Jiang Yifan,

00:31:03.290 --> 00:31:05.180
do you realize how amazing you are?

00:31:07.050 --> 00:31:08.900
You fulfill all my imaginations

00:31:08.900 --> 00:31:10.010
of an ideal girl.

00:31:12.090 --> 00:31:13.770
I have no reason to reject you.

00:31:14.620 --> 00:31:15.570
Open the door!

00:31:16.770 --> 00:31:17.700
Stop talking.

00:31:20.180 --> 00:31:21.250
Don't make me look down on you.

00:31:23.620 --> 00:31:25.530
Is it embarrassing
to have feelings for someone?

00:31:27.050 --> 00:31:28.620
But you did it
behind your girlfriend's back.

00:31:29.220 --> 00:31:30.620
Seeing you professing love to others

00:31:32.140 --> 00:31:33.380
makes me sick.

00:31:41.530 --> 00:31:42.370
Is that so?

00:31:44.490 --> 00:31:45.380
Yu He,

00:31:45.860 --> 00:31:46.730
listen carefully!

00:31:48.380 --> 00:31:50.090
From now on, we're over.

00:31:51.010 --> 00:31:52.900
I'm sorry I can't keep loving you.

00:31:55.180 --> 00:31:57.180
I've fallen for this girl
named Jiang Yifan.

00:31:58.620 --> 00:32:00.010
Thank you for letting me meet her.

00:32:02.010 --> 00:32:03.050
What did you say?

00:32:03.810 --> 00:32:05.010
Say it again.

00:32:06.660 --> 00:32:07.900
